### 1️⃣ Registro ufficiale dei contributi (DB + API)

#### 1.1 Schema PostgreSQL  

```sql
CREATE TABLE contributions (
    id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    author_id       UUID NOT NULL,
    contribution_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,   -- 'paper','prototype','lecture',…
    title           TEXT NOT NULL,
    uri             TEXT NOT NULL,            -- link a PDF, repo, DOI
    impact_metric   NUMERIC,                  -- citazioni, download, ecc.
    created_at      TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT now(),
    approved        BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
);
```

#### 1.2 Endpoint FastAPI (Python)  

```python
from fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException
from pydantic import BaseModel, HttpUrl, UUID4
import asyncpg

app = FastAPI()
db = None  # sarà inizializzato al startup

class ContributionIn(BaseModel):
    author_id: UUID4
    contribution_type: str
    title: str
    uri: HttpUrl
    impact_metric: float | None = None

@app.on_event("startup")
async def init_db():
    global db
    db = await asyncpg.create_pool(dsn="postgresql://user:pwd@db/nexus")

@app.post("/contributions", status_code=201)
async def add_contribution(c: ContributionIn):
    async with db.acquire() as conn:
        await conn.execute(
            """
            INSERT INTO contributions (author_id, contribution_type, title, uri, impact_metric)
            VALUES ($1,$2,$3,$4,$5)
            """,
            c.author_id, c.contribution_type, c.title, str(c.uri), c.impact_metric,
        )
    return {"msg":"contribution recorded"}
```

*Ogni progetto, paper o prototipo di Hannes dovrà essere inserito qui; il comitato approverà (`approved = true`) prima della successiva distribuzione di compensi.*

